<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4A645693FD4FFE27" box="[596,746,447,471]" captionStart="PLATE 10" captionStartId="43.[151,233,1994,2017]" captionTargetBox="[186,1414,186,1982]" captionTargetId="figure-41@43.[166,1430,151,2005]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="PLATE 10. Crovettia masneri, holotype. A. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.4 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278404/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 10A, B</figureCitation>
); epistomal suture situated at same level of antennal toruli (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA489056C8FEA4FE0C" box="[160,257,484,508]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="12.[151,233,1929,1952]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,362,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-172@12.[188,1412,357,1934]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="PLATE 4. A, B, E. Males. C, D. Male genitalia. b, basivolsella; d, distivolsella; k, dorsal process of paramere; o, paramere; p, penis or aedeagus. F, G. Heads. A. Dryinus sp. Length 3.0 mm. B. Occiput of Gonatopus sp. C. Dryinus sp. D. Echthrodelphax sp. E. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. F.Aphelopus sp. G. Crovettia sp. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278384" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278384/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 4G</figureCitation>
); occipital carina complete; antenna without rhinaria; palpal formula 5/2, or 5/3, or 6/2, or 6/3; fore wing with only costal cell enclosed by pigmented veins (as in plate 11A, B) or with costal and medial cells completely enclosed by pigmented veins (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA49C15500FD21FDB3" box="[497,644,556,580]" captionStart="PLATE 10" captionStartId="43.[151,233,1994,2017]" captionTargetBox="[186,1414,186,1982]" captionTargetId="figure-41@43.[166,1430,151,2005]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="PLATE 10. Crovettia masneri, holotype. A. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.4 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278404/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 10A, B</figureCitation>
); fore wing with pterostigma present (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4C0C5500FB6AFDB3" box="[1084,1231,556,580]" captionStart="PLATE 10" captionStartId="43.[151,233,1994,2017]" captionTargetBox="[186,1414,186,1982]" captionTargetId="figure-41@43.[166,1430,151,2005]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="PLATE 10. Crovettia masneri, holotype. A. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.4 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278404/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 10A, B</figureCitation>
) and stigmal vein straight (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA48CE5563FECAFD97" box="[254,367,591,615]" captionStart="PLATE 11" captionStartId="45.[151,233,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[226,1387,258,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-101@45.[198,1403,238,1954]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="PLATE 11. Crovettia townesi, holotype. A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.0 mm. C. Maxillary palpus. D. Labial palpus. E. Mandible. F. Male genitalia. Scale bar 0.37 mm for C, 0.32 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and 0.13 mm for F. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278406/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 11A</figureCitation>
), or forming an angle between the proximal and distal parts (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4C0D5563FB3BFD97" box="[1085,1182,591,615]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="12.[151,233,1929,1952]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,362,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-172@12.[188,1412,357,1934]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="PLATE 4. A, B, E. Males. C, D. Male genitalia. b, basivolsella; d, distivolsella; k, dorsal process of paramere; o, paramere; p, penis or aedeagus. F, G. Heads. A. Dryinus sp. Length 3.0 mm. B. Occiput of Gonatopus sp. C. Dryinus sp. D. Echthrodelphax sp. E. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. F.Aphelopus sp. G. Crovettia sp. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278384" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278384/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 4E</figureCitation>
); course of fore wing veins not marked by dark stripes (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4A1B5558FD67FD7B" box="[555,706,628,652]" captionStart="PLATE 10" captionStartId="43.[151,233,1994,2017]" captionTargetBox="[186,1414,186,1982]" captionTargetId="figure-41@43.[166,1430,151,2005]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="PLATE 10. Crovettia masneri, holotype. A. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.4 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278404/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 10A, B</figureCitation>
); hindwing (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4B6C5558FC6BFD7C" box="[860,974,628,652]" captionStart="PLATE 10" captionStartId="43.[151,233,1994,2017]" captionTargetBox="[186,1414,186,1982]" captionTargetId="figure-41@43.[166,1430,151,2005]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="PLATE 10. Crovettia masneri, holotype. A. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.4 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278404/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 10A</figureCitation>
) hyaline, with costal cell, without dark medial longitudinal stripe; protarsus not chelate (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4AF455BBFCF3FD5F" box="[708,854,663,687]" captionStart="PLATE 10" captionStartId="43.[151,233,1994,2017]" captionTargetBox="[186,1414,186,1982]" captionTargetId="figure-41@43.[166,1430,151,2005]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="PLATE 10. Crovettia masneri, holotype. A. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.4 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278404/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 10A, B</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/1/2. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E64FFEA4C0C55B4FBD0FD40" box="[1084,1141,664,688]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Male</emphasis>
: fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4D1655BBFF0FFD23" captionStart="PLATE 11" captionStartId="45.[151,233,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[226,1387,258,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-101@45.[198,1403,238,1954]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="PLATE 11. Crovettia townesi, holotype. A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.0 mm. C. Maxillary palpus. D. Labial palpus. E. Mandible. F. Male genitalia. Scale bar 0.37 mm for C, 0.32 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and 0.13 mm for F. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278406/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 11A, B</figureCitation>
); epistomal suture situated below imaginary line joining antennal toruli (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4BC75590FBFFFD24" box="[1015,1114,700,724]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="12.[151,233,1929,1952]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,362,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-172@12.[188,1412,357,1934]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="PLATE 4. A, B, E. Males. C, D. Male genitalia. b, basivolsella; d, distivolsella; k, dorsal process of paramere; o, paramere; p, penis or aedeagus. F, G. Heads. A. Dryinus sp. Length 3.0 mm. B. Occiput of Gonatopus sp. C. Dryinus sp. D. Echthrodelphax sp. E. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. F.Aphelopus sp. G. Crovettia sp. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278384" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278384/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 4G</figureCitation>
); occipital carina complete; palpal formula 5/2, or 5/3, or 6/2, or 6/3; fore wing with only costal cell enclosed by pigmented veins (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4D1655F3FF0FFCEB" captionStart="PLATE 11" captionStartId="45.[151,233,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[226,1387,258,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-101@45.[198,1403,238,1954]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="PLATE 11. Crovettia townesi, holotype. A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.0 mm. C. Maxillary palpus. D. Labial palpus. E. Mandible. F. Male genitalia. Scale bar 0.37 mm for C, 0.32 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and 0.13 mm for F. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278406/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 11A, B</figureCitation>
) or with costal and medial cells completely enclosed by pigmented veins (as in plate 10A, B); fore wing with pterostigma present (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA49B2540BFDB4FCCF" box="[386,529,807,831]" captionStart="PLATE 11" captionStartId="45.[151,233,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[226,1387,258,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-101@45.[198,1403,238,1954]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="PLATE 11. Crovettia townesi, holotype. A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.0 mm. C. Maxillary palpus. D. Labial palpus. E. Mandible. F. Male genitalia. Scale bar 0.37 mm for C, 0.32 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and 0.13 mm for F. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278406/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 11A, B</figureCitation>
) and stigmal vein straight (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4B73540BFC15FCCF" box="[835,944,807,831]" captionStart="PLATE 11" captionStartId="45.[151,233,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[226,1387,258,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-101@45.[198,1403,238,1954]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="PLATE 11. Crovettia townesi, holotype. A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.0 mm. C. Maxillary palpus. D. Labial palpus. E. Mandible. F. Male genitalia. Scale bar 0.37 mm for C, 0.32 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and 0.13 mm for F. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278406/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 11A</figureCitation>
), or forming an angle between the proximal and distal parts (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA49605460FE0BFC94" box="[336,430,844,868]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="12.[151,233,1929,1952]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,362,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-172@12.[188,1412,357,1934]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="PLATE 4. A, B, E. Males. C, D. Male genitalia. b, basivolsella; d, distivolsella; k, dorsal process of paramere; o, paramere; p, penis or aedeagus. F, G. Heads. A. Dryinus sp. Length 3.0 mm. B. Occiput of Gonatopus sp. C. Dryinus sp. D. Echthrodelphax sp. E. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. F.Aphelopus sp. G. Crovettia sp. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278384" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278384/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 4E</figureCitation>
); course of fore wing veins not marked by dark stripes (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4C145460FB37FC94" box="[1060,1170,844,868]" captionStart="PLATE 11" captionStartId="45.[151,233,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[226,1387,258,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-101@45.[198,1403,238,1954]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="PLATE 11. Crovettia townesi, holotype. A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.0 mm. C. Maxillary palpus. D. Labial palpus. E. Mandible. F. Male genitalia. Scale bar 0.37 mm for C, 0.32 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and 0.13 mm for F. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278406/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 11A</figureCitation>
); hindwing (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA4D145460FA37FC94" box="[1316,1426,844,868]" captionStart="PLATE 11" captionStartId="45.[151,233,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[226,1387,258,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-101@45.[198,1403,238,1954]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="PLATE 11. Crovettia townesi, holotype. A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.0 mm. C. Maxillary palpus. D. Labial palpus. E. Mandible. F. Male genitalia. Scale bar 0.37 mm for C, 0.32 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and 0.13 mm for F. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278406/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 11A</figureCitation>
) hyaline, with costal cell, without dark medial longitudinal stripe; basivolsella completely situated down distivolsella distal apex (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA499E54B8FDB2FC5C" box="[430,535,916,940]" captionStart="PLATE 11" captionStartId="45.[151,233,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[226,1387,258,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-101@45.[198,1403,238,1954]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="PLATE 11. Crovettia townesi, holotype. A, B. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.0 mm. C. Maxillary palpus. D. Labial palpus. E. Mandible. F. Male genitalia. Scale bar 0.37 mm for C, 0.32 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and 0.13 mm for F. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278406/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 11F</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E64FFEA48F7549BFC50FC04" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="007606418E64FFEA48F7549BFC50FC04" blockId="42.[151,1437,411,1084]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E64FFEA48F7549BFEC5FC20" bold="true" box="[199,352,951,976]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Distribution.</emphasis>
Present in the Oriental, Nearctic, Neotropical and Australian regions. Never collected in the Afrotropical region. Present at the Oriental border of the Palaearctic (
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E64FFEA4B9054F0FC4CFC04" box="[928,1001,988,1012]" name="Nepal" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Nepal</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E64FFEA48F7532CFC70FBCC" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="007606418E64FFEA48F7532CFCA6FBE7" blockId="42.[151,1437,411,1084]" box="[199,771,1023,1048]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E64FFEA48F7532CFEB4FBE8" bold="true" box="[199,273,1024,1048]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Hosts.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E64FFEA492854D3FD5AFBE7" authority="(Guglielmino &amp; Olmi, 1997)" baseAuthorityName="Guglielmino &amp; Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[280,767,1023,1047]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Membracidae (
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08E64FFEA49F054D3FD52FBE7" author="Guglielmino &amp; Olmi" box="[448,759,1023,1047]" firstAuthor="Guglielmino" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="165 - 298" refId="ref360036" refString="Guglielmino, A. &amp; Olmi, M. (1997) A host-parasite catalog of world Dryinidae (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea). Contributions on Entomology, International, 2 (2), 165 - 298." type="journal article" year="1997">Guglielmino &amp; Olmi, 1997</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E64FFEA48F75308FC70FBCC" blockId="42.[151,1437,411,1084]" box="[199,981,1059,1084]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E64FFEA48F75308FED1FBCC" bold="true" box="[199,372,1059,1084]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">World species.</emphasis>
Fifteen species are known, two in the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38E64FFEA4B135308FC74FBCC" box="[803,977,1060,1084]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
